WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.500
[Ambient: wind howling, radio static crackling]

00:00:04.500 --> 00:00:10.000
NARRATOR: The Arctic station had been running on autopilot
for eleven months when Marcus first heard it.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:15.500
A voice — low and deliberate — threading through the static
like smoke through a keyhole.

00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:19.000
[Static increases sharply, then drops]

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:27.000
VOICE (distorted): ...if anyone receives this, the coordinates
are seventy-three north, forty-one west. Do not come alone.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:35.500
MARCUS: Station log, day three-forty-two.
I've been at this post long enough to know
the difference between interference and intention.

00:00:35.500 --> 00:00:39.000
That was intention.

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:44.000
[Sound of a chair scraping, then silence]

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:52.000
MARCUS: I'm going to play it back. Starting trace protocol now.
If this log is ever read by someone other than me —
it means I found something.

00:00:52.000 --> 00:01:00.000
[Theme music begins — low synthesizer drone with distant choral elements]
